h33 y618 ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">head, and you will strike his heel” <span class="ff11">(Genesis 3:15, NIV).</span></div><div class="t m0 x45 h35 y619 ff12 fs27 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">A </div><div class="t m0 x8 h36 y61a ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws13f">comic used to play a female character called Geraldine. In one </div><div class="t m0 x8 h36 y61b ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws131">monologue she was a minister’s wife who had come home </div><div class="t m0 x8 h36 y619 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws147">with an expensive new dress. Her husband (played by the </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y61c ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws1e">same comedian) got angry. Geraldine then shrieked in response: “The </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y61d ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws96">devil made me buy this dress! I didn’t want to buy the dress. The devil </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y61e ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">kept bothering me.” </div><div class="t m0 x58 h36 y61f ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws12a">That was supposed to be funny. But our world, and the evil in it, </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y620 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">shows that Satan is no laughing matter.</div><div class="t m0 x58 h36 y621 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws148">For some people, the idea of the devil is an ancient superstition </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y622 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws36">not to be taken seriously. Scripture, however, is unequivocal: though </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y623 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wsa8">Satan is a defeated foe <span class="ff11">(Rev. 12:12, 1 John 3:8)</span>, he is here on the </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y624 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws62">earth, and he is determined to wreak as much havoc and destruction </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y625 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">as possible against God’s creation. </div><div class="t m0 x58 h36 y626 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wsb3">This week we’ll look at Satan’s original attack and what we can </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y627 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws28">learn from it so that while we are still under his assault, we can claim </div><div class="t m0 x45 h36 y628 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">the victory that’s ours in Christ. </div><div class="t m0 x3b h33 y629 ff11 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">*Study this week’s lesson to prepare for Sabbath, February 9.</div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
